start-details:

h2: Data Cleansing Node

h4: Overview:

The Data Cleansing node performs various data cleaning operations on a DataFrame, including:

Removing Null Values: Removes rows or columns with null values.
Replacing Null Values: Replaces null values with a specified value.
Removing Unwanted Characters: Removes specific characters or patterns from text columns.
Matching Case: Converts text to uppercase or lowercase.
h4: Input:

Selected Columns: A list of columns to apply the cleaning operations to.
h4: Output:

The cleaned DataFrame with the specified operations applied to the selected columns.

end-details:

start-examples:

Example:

Let's assume we have a DataFrame with the following columns: id, column1, column2, column3, column4, column5, column6, column7, column8.

We want to:

Remove rows where column1 is null.
Replace null values in column2 with 0.
Remove extra spaces from column3.
Convert column4 to uppercase.
Configuration:

Selected Columns: column1, column2, column3, column4
Node Execution:

The node will apply the following operations to the selected columns:

Remove rows where column1 is null.
Replace null values in column2 with 0.
Trim extra spaces from column3.
Convert column4 to uppercase.

end-examples:
